			<a name="example"></a>
			<h1 class="title">Example Of Use</h1>
			<p class="description">After choosing the desaired service, a HTTP POST request may be made. To do that, it is advised by us to see all the information related to the service like the required parameters to successfully return something. To use any of our service it is needed a token that can be obtained with a simple authentication in the platform.</p>
			<p class="description">How to do it with an easy curl command:</p>
			<p class="code">curl -i -F "text=Any sentence you want." -F "api_token=your_token" http://spline.di-um.org/tokenizer</p>
			<p class="description">You can send this type of request with text, numbers and files too.</p>
			<p class="code">curl -i -F "file=@path/file" -F "api_token=your_token" http://spline.di-um.org/nat-create</p>
		</div>
		<br/><br/>
